1
00:01:33,625 --> 00:01:35,065
You don't have to talk.

2
00:01:39,785 --> 00:01:41,785
Just listen to my heartbeat.

3
00:02:36,225 --> 00:02:40,425
Will you let me set the rhythm
for us tonight?

4
00:03:29,105 --> 00:03:32,345
MOM

5
00:03:53,625 --> 00:03:54,865
Yes, Mom?

6
00:03:58,465 --> 00:04:01,105
What? You're outside the house right now?

7
00:04:05,265 --> 00:04:07,505
Why didn't you call me first?

8
00:04:07,585 --> 00:04:09,505
What if I wasn't home?

9
00:04:09,585 --> 00:04:10,905
It doesn't matter, Runch.

10
00:04:10,985 --> 00:04:13,625
If you weren't home,
I'd just give this to the maid.

11
00:04:14,625 --> 00:04:16,944
Don't worry.
I wasn't going to talk to your wife.

12
00:04:17,025 --> 00:04:18,745
I'd never want to anyway.

13
00:04:18,825 --> 00:04:19,985
Mom.

14
00:04:20,944 --> 00:04:22,105
Where is she, though?

15
00:04:24,505 --> 00:04:27,305
It's her day off. She's still sleeping.

16
00:04:28,185 --> 00:04:31,825
If you hadn't come,
I'd still be sleeping too.

17
00:04:32,425 --> 00:04:34,145
Since when did you start sleeping in?

18
00:04:37,825 --> 00:04:39,345
Want to join us for breakfast, Mom?

19
00:04:40,705 --> 00:04:43,465
I'm good. I already ate with your dad.

20
00:04:43,545 --> 00:04:45,625
Do you want to eat now?
I'll reheat it for you.

21
00:04:45,705 --> 00:04:47,225
-Just a second.
-It's okay, Mom.

22
00:04:47,305 --> 00:04:48,225
What?

23
00:04:48,305 --> 00:04:50,865
-I can do it myself.
-It's okay, honey.

24
00:04:50,945 --> 00:04:54,425
It's your day off.
You should sit back and relax.

25
00:04:54,505 --> 00:04:55,865
I'll handle it for you.

26
00:04:55,945 --> 00:04:58,905
Who cares if your wife
doesn't take care of you? I can do it too.

27
00:04:58,985 --> 00:05:01,545
Neen has a job too, Mom.

28
00:05:01,625 --> 00:05:05,785
And it's not her duty
to handle these things anyway.

29
00:05:05,865 --> 00:05:09,025
I don't expect her to do it alone.

30
00:05:09,105 --> 00:05:12,785
What's her job?
Does she work as hard as my daughter?

31
00:05:12,865 --> 00:05:15,465
Has that brat ever accomplished anything?

32
00:05:15,545 --> 00:05:18,185
She's always dressed up all nice,
and just saunters around.

33
00:05:18,265 --> 00:05:20,665
When will you stop criticizing her, Mom?

34
00:05:20,745 --> 00:05:22,705
Ugh, Runch.

35
00:05:22,785 --> 00:05:25,505
You're always blindly defending your wife!

36
00:05:25,585 --> 00:05:29,145
Just admit you made a bad decision
and ended up with a bad wife!

37
00:05:30,665 --> 00:05:31,825
How am I a bad wife?

38
00:05:41,025 --> 00:05:44,945
Your daughter really loves me though, Mom.

39
00:05:48,345 --> 00:05:49,625
Anyway,

40
00:05:50,345 --> 00:05:52,905
what are you doing in my house this early?

41
00:05:54,665 --> 00:05:58,025
Is that how sophisticated people
greet others?

42
00:05:59,065 --> 00:06:01,825
And look at your clothes.
You look like a tramp.

43
00:06:01,905 --> 00:06:03,745
Don't you have anything better to wear?

44
00:06:05,185 --> 00:06:08,185
Or is this how rich kids like to dress?

45
00:06:09,145 --> 00:06:11,785
Actually, I don't like
wearing these clothes.

46
00:06:12,425 --> 00:06:13,865
But Runch…

47
00:06:14,785 --> 00:06:17,745
Runch likes it.
She says they're easy to take off.

48
00:06:17,825 --> 00:06:21,025
Yuck. Gross! Disgusting!

49
00:06:21,105 --> 00:06:22,745
Enough, Mom.

50
00:06:24,265 --> 00:06:25,865
And you slept in until late morning.

51
00:06:27,105 --> 00:06:30,185
If I hadn't come today,
my daughter wouldn't get to eat.

52
00:06:30,265 --> 00:06:34,585
Ugh. Mom, your daughter
can find her own food.

53
00:06:34,665 --> 00:06:36,105
She finds it for me too.

54
00:06:36,185 --> 00:06:38,545
Are you disabled?
Why do you have to rely on her?

55
00:06:38,625 --> 00:06:40,905
I'm not disabled, Mom.

56
00:06:40,985 --> 00:06:45,225
What I am is Runch's little cutie pie.

57
00:06:45,305 --> 00:06:47,505
My goodness!

58
00:06:47,585 --> 00:06:49,745
Are you that submissive
to this brat, Runch?

59
00:06:49,825 --> 00:06:53,145
She's even more submissive to me
than you think, Mom.

60
00:06:53,225 --> 00:06:56,185
She does everything I tell her.

61
00:06:58,305 --> 00:07:01,225
Runch loves following
her wife's orders. Right?

62
00:07:02,265 --> 00:07:04,305
-I can't take any more of this!
-Enough!

63
00:07:04,385 --> 00:07:05,625
Mom, go home already!

64
00:07:06,785 --> 00:07:07,745
Runch!

65
00:07:07,825 --> 00:07:09,865
Did you just tell me to leave?!

66
00:07:10,545 --> 00:07:12,265
That's not it.

67
00:07:12,785 --> 00:07:14,305
But you really should go home.

68
00:07:14,385 --> 00:07:16,505
Come on. I'll walk you.

69
00:07:17,065 --> 00:07:17,905
Come on.

70
00:07:18,425 --> 00:07:20,345
-Mom.
-You crazy brat!

71
00:07:20,425 --> 00:07:21,825
Mom!

72
00:07:22,665 --> 00:07:23,945
Come on, Runch!

73
00:07:26,065 --> 00:07:27,185
Mom.

74
00:07:28,345 --> 00:07:31,145
What's the matter with you, Runch?
Why'd you tell me to leave?

75
00:07:31,225 --> 00:07:32,185
Mom,

76
00:07:33,225 --> 00:07:34,225
that's enough.

77
00:07:34,305 --> 00:07:36,265
This is exactly why

78
00:07:36,345 --> 00:07:39,305
I told you to tell me before you come.

79
00:07:39,385 --> 00:07:40,865
This is your house too,

80
00:07:41,385 --> 00:07:44,265
so why do I need to tell you?
Why do I need permission?

81
00:07:44,345 --> 00:07:46,425
It's not my house.

82
00:07:46,505 --> 00:07:50,465
Rin's parents bought it
for our marriage. Don't forget that.

83
00:07:50,545 --> 00:07:52,865
And that's why she has such a nerve.

84
00:07:53,545 --> 00:07:55,185
Enough, Mom!

85
00:07:55,265 --> 00:07:58,465
This is why I didn't want you to come.

86
00:07:59,065 --> 00:08:00,745
Well, your wife started it!

87
00:08:00,825 --> 00:08:04,345
No. Stop it, Mom. She didn't start it.

88
00:08:04,425 --> 00:08:06,145
-Runch!
-Mom.

89
00:08:06,785 --> 00:08:08,185
Please go home.

90
00:08:08,265 --> 00:08:11,225
-Please. Please?
-Runch!

91
00:08:11,305 --> 00:08:14,305
Fine. I'll go home for now.
Just because you asked.

92
00:08:51,145 --> 00:08:52,305
Neen.

93
00:08:52,985 --> 00:08:55,025
Let's go upstairs,
get changed, and then eat.

94
00:08:55,105 --> 00:08:56,425
I don't want to.

95
00:08:57,305 --> 00:08:59,465
-Aren't you hungry?
-Leave me alone.

96
00:09:00,825 --> 00:09:03,825
And this house isn't yours alone.

97
00:09:03,905 --> 00:09:06,665
Please ask me before you welcome a guest.

98
00:09:06,745 --> 00:09:09,785
Stop letting that old loudmouth
come in and insult me!

99
00:09:09,865 --> 00:09:11,225
It's happened too many times.

100
00:09:11,305 --> 00:09:12,345
Neen.

101
00:09:13,105 --> 00:09:15,065
-That's my mom you're talking about.
-So?

102
00:09:15,745 --> 00:09:19,545
So she can insult me
but I can't do it to her?

103
00:09:21,145 --> 00:09:23,785
Or do you only allow me to be insulted?

104
00:09:27,505 --> 00:09:30,345
I'm sorry. Really.

105
00:09:32,305 --> 00:09:34,265
That's just how my mom is.

106
00:09:34,345 --> 00:09:36,465
She doesn't listen
when I tell her or warn her.

107
00:09:36,545 --> 00:09:40,585
So you're telling me, warning me,
and disciplining me instead?

108
00:09:51,865 --> 00:09:53,545
Aren't you tired, Neen?

109
00:09:55,025 --> 00:09:57,425
You always fight with my mom
every time you meet.

110
00:09:58,985 --> 00:10:00,065
Of course I am.

111
00:10:00,745 --> 00:10:03,345
I'm tired of both you and her.

112
00:10:03,425 --> 00:10:06,025
But you know what? She's only this way

113
00:10:06,105 --> 00:10:08,785
because you're her enabler.
I hope you know that.

114
00:10:08,865 --> 00:10:11,505
When your mom
does bad things, acts rudely,

115
00:10:11,585 --> 00:10:15,105
or does what normal people wouldn't do,
please discipline her.

116
00:10:16,065 --> 00:10:19,705
Because if you don't, I'll do it myself.

117
00:10:19,785 --> 00:10:22,905
Fighting all the time can take a toll
on our mental health.

118
00:10:23,625 --> 00:10:26,145
I can't stand this kind of environment.

119
00:10:27,465 --> 00:10:29,985
Well, that old loudmouth
is always insulting me.

120
00:10:30,065 --> 00:10:32,585
Your mom's like a crazy dog
who bites everyone,

121
00:10:32,665 --> 00:10:34,905
yet you expect to have a peaceful life?

122
00:10:34,985 --> 00:10:35,985
Neen!

123
00:10:49,865 --> 00:10:52,425
I'm sorry.

124
00:10:53,825 --> 00:10:55,065
I didn't mean to yell at you.

125
00:10:55,985 --> 00:10:57,905
You're angry because I insulted your mom,

126
00:10:57,985 --> 00:11:01,105
but do you ever care when she insults me?

127
00:11:05,785 --> 00:11:07,545
You're just so good at everything.

128
00:11:10,305 --> 00:11:11,825
Everyone admires you.

129
00:11:11,905 --> 00:11:14,745
You have a great career,
and you're good at your job.

130
00:11:15,785 --> 00:11:19,145
You seem so great to everyone.

131
00:11:19,945 --> 00:11:22,825
But you know what? As your wife

132
00:11:22,905 --> 00:11:26,545
who's in this relationship with you,
I think you're the worst!

133
00:11:31,465 --> 00:11:35,385
I regret it. I regret nothing more
than deciding to marry you.

134
00:11:36,825 --> 00:11:39,785
If I could turn back time,
I never would've married you.

135
00:11:44,185 --> 00:11:45,225
I'm sorry.

136
00:11:46,225 --> 00:11:50,345
You once told me you wanted a divorce.
I want one too.

137
00:11:52,265 --> 00:11:54,425
But for now, while we're still married,

138
00:11:55,105 --> 00:11:57,425
can you be a good wife for me?

139
00:11:57,945 --> 00:12:01,065
At least during this extra time
that my family asked for,

140
00:12:02,785 --> 00:12:04,625
please pretend we still love each other.

141
00:12:06,185 --> 00:12:07,385
Can you let me

142
00:12:07,465 --> 00:12:10,985
break your mom's heart
just once in my lifetime?

143
00:12:11,065 --> 00:12:13,465
At least just for a little longer.

144
00:12:19,385 --> 00:12:20,545
Neen.

145
00:12:54,025 --> 00:12:56,545
<i>Are you sure about getting divorced?</i>

146
00:12:57,225 --> 00:13:00,585
<i>Yes. We've talked about it.</i>

147
00:13:01,225 --> 00:13:05,185
I never expected to hear
you both say it so easily.

148
00:13:06,505 --> 00:13:08,025
You're adults now.

149
00:13:09,225 --> 00:13:10,745
You've matured.

150
00:13:13,305 --> 00:13:14,585
But, oh well.

151
00:13:15,505 --> 00:13:17,625
I trust that you've thought it over.

152
00:13:21,505 --> 00:13:23,625
There's just one thing
I want to ask of you.

153
00:13:25,385 --> 00:13:26,665
It's very important.

154
00:13:32,545 --> 00:13:35,865
Don't tell anyone
you're getting divorced yet.

155
00:13:37,345 --> 00:13:39,345
Not even your own family, Runch.

156
00:13:41,025 --> 00:13:44,505
I want no one other than the people here
to know about this.

157
00:13:45,905 --> 00:13:49,745
Another one of Iperis' restaurants
is about to open in four months.

158
00:13:51,025 --> 00:13:53,385
The press will be present,
and so will our partners.

159
00:13:53,465 --> 00:13:55,985
There'll be a big event
for our company and our family.

160
00:13:57,625 --> 00:14:00,985
And we need to use
the public image of a stable marriage

161
00:14:01,505 --> 00:14:03,185
for news stories about the event.

162
00:14:05,665 --> 00:14:07,065
I want just four months.

163
00:14:07,985 --> 00:14:09,505
Can you do that for me?

164
00:14:18,785 --> 00:14:19,705
Sure.

165
00:14:23,585 --> 00:14:24,465
Thank you.

166
00:14:26,065 --> 00:14:27,865
I know it's hard.

167
00:14:28,945 --> 00:14:30,145
But I promise you.

168
00:14:30,785 --> 00:14:34,945
After four months,
no matter what your decision is,

169
00:14:35,585 --> 00:14:37,305
I won't stop you anymore.

170
00:15:01,945 --> 00:15:03,385
Natee.

171
00:15:03,465 --> 00:15:06,385
Looks like
I'll have to divorce Neen for real.

172
00:15:06,465 --> 00:15:09,025
<i>Huh? Divorce?</i>

173
00:15:09,105 --> 00:15:10,505
Are you being serious?

174
00:15:11,545 --> 00:15:13,225
This is a big deal, you know.

175
00:15:13,305 --> 00:15:15,905
You two really love each other, though.
What happened?

176
00:15:15,985 --> 00:15:19,265
Every time my mom and Neen meet,

177
00:15:20,105 --> 00:15:23,665
it feels like I have to watch
two people I love

178
00:15:24,345 --> 00:15:26,025
hurt each other repeatedly.

179
00:15:27,185 --> 00:15:29,305
I want to defend both of them.

180
00:15:31,985 --> 00:15:33,665
But in the end,

181
00:15:33,745 --> 00:15:35,585
I could never do anything.

182
00:15:36,105 --> 00:15:38,025
I could never defend either of them.

183
00:15:39,025 --> 00:15:40,825
<i>Neen's really tired, Natee.</i>

184
00:15:40,905 --> 00:15:42,825
<i>She's already tired from work,</i>

185
00:15:42,905 --> 00:15:46,745
and my mom and I tire her even more.

186
00:15:47,545 --> 00:15:50,025
She has to try to act tough

187
00:15:51,385 --> 00:15:54,385
when she's actually
a really sensitive person.

188
00:15:54,945 --> 00:15:57,865
Every time I see my mom insult Neen,

189
00:15:59,225 --> 00:16:01,865
she's got that childlike look in her eyes,

190
00:16:03,105 --> 00:16:05,185
like a child
who feels hurt and unaccepted.

191
00:16:05,785 --> 00:16:08,745
I really love Neen, Natee.

192
00:16:10,785 --> 00:16:12,505
I love her so much

193
00:16:13,105 --> 00:16:16,705
that I don't think
I can ever love anyone as much.

194
00:16:17,785 --> 00:16:19,225
<i>But the more I love her,</i>

195
00:16:19,865 --> 00:16:21,145
<i>the more I know</i>

196
00:16:21,225 --> 00:16:24,145
that it's because of me

197
00:16:24,945 --> 00:16:27,785
that she has to suffer because of my mom.

198
00:16:29,225 --> 00:16:30,945
<i>I didn't ask for a divorce</i>

199
00:16:31,465 --> 00:16:34,145
<i>because I fell out of love, Natee.</i>

200
00:16:34,225 --> 00:16:35,785
<i>It was because…</i>

201
00:16:37,505 --> 00:16:39,225
<i>I really love Neen,</i>

202
00:16:40,345 --> 00:16:41,665
<i>so much</i>

203
00:16:42,825 --> 00:16:46,425
that I'd walk away
from this relationship myself.

204
00:16:49,745 --> 00:16:51,945
This way, I won't hurt her anymore.

205
00:17:08,464 --> 00:17:10,105
Why are you back so soon, honey?

206
00:17:11,224 --> 00:17:14,184
Runch told me to leave
because of that brat.

207
00:17:14,265 --> 00:17:17,025
Did you have a fight with Neen again?

208
00:17:17,105 --> 00:17:20,145
How many times
have I told you not to do that?

209
00:17:20,224 --> 00:17:23,585
If you keep this up
and Runch can't take it anymore,

210
00:17:23,665 --> 00:17:25,065
just don't say I didn't warn you.

211
00:17:25,145 --> 00:17:26,985
She may not speak a lot,

212
00:17:27,065 --> 00:17:29,865
but you'd better watch out.
One day she'll run out of patience.

213
00:17:30,505 --> 00:17:32,465
Runch has been aggressive
since they got married.

214
00:17:32,545 --> 00:17:35,505
This is exactly why
I didn't want her to marry that brat!

215
00:17:35,585 --> 00:17:38,625
I don't see how Neen is that bad at all.

216
00:17:38,705 --> 00:17:40,505
And you too, Pong.

217
00:17:40,585 --> 00:17:42,705
Why do you love
your daughter-in-law so much?

218
00:17:42,785 --> 00:17:44,385
And don't you threaten me.

219
00:17:44,465 --> 00:17:48,025
If Runch ever feels unhappy with me,
I'm still her mom.

220
00:17:48,825 --> 00:17:50,185
You sure seem confident.

221
00:17:50,265 --> 00:17:52,265
I think when people
have a family of their own,

222
00:17:52,345 --> 00:17:55,505
they'll always prioritize their family.

223
00:17:56,305 --> 00:17:58,505
That's why I didn't want her
to get married.

224
00:18:00,665 --> 00:18:02,865
You want her to marry
someone you like, don't you?

225
00:18:02,945 --> 00:18:05,425
At least then I can rest a little easy

226
00:18:05,505 --> 00:18:07,425
if she marries someone
who gets along with me.

227
00:18:07,505 --> 00:18:10,345
You always made sarcastic
and snide remarks

228
00:18:10,425 --> 00:18:12,025
even when they were just dating,

229
00:18:12,105 --> 00:18:14,785
just because you didn't like her,
and you didn't get your way.

230
00:18:14,865 --> 00:18:17,545
Now that she's fed up
and starts retaliating,

231
00:18:17,625 --> 00:18:19,665
you're saying she's the bad guy?

232
00:18:20,625 --> 00:18:24,305
When was I ever being sarcastic?
Everything I said is true.

233
00:18:24,385 --> 00:18:26,425
Neen's just a rich kid who's incompetent.

234
00:18:26,505 --> 00:18:28,065
She'll only give Runch a hard time.

235
00:18:28,145 --> 00:18:31,705
And she shows way too much skin.
How unladylike!

236
00:18:31,785 --> 00:18:35,145
She's a clubber, and she's too bougie.
She's not ladylike at all!

237
00:18:35,225 --> 00:18:38,585
I don't care how rich she is.
She's not fit to be Runch's partner.

238
00:18:38,665 --> 00:18:41,305
She doesn't support Runch
in any way! Damn it!

239
00:19:09,705 --> 00:19:12,425
My mom called
and invited us over for dinner.

240
00:19:12,505 --> 00:19:14,025
Well, she does it every week.

241
00:19:14,545 --> 00:19:17,305
But if you don't want to go,
then don't. I'll go alone.

242
00:19:17,865 --> 00:19:20,505
I never said I didn't want to go.

243
00:19:23,025 --> 00:19:25,185
My parents understand.

244
00:19:25,265 --> 00:19:27,585
They know we're about to get divorced.

245
00:19:28,105 --> 00:19:30,305
You don't have to pretend
you still love me

246
00:19:30,385 --> 00:19:32,705
like you do in front of your family.

247
00:19:40,345 --> 00:19:42,145
We aren't divorced yet,

248
00:19:42,785 --> 00:19:45,985
so can't I have dinner
with my parents-in-law?

249
00:19:47,825 --> 00:19:48,825
Suit yourself.

250
00:19:59,425 --> 00:20:01,185
You're always in denial and unforgiving.

251
00:20:01,265 --> 00:20:03,705
That's why she asked for a divorce.

252
00:20:04,345 --> 00:20:05,985
Why are you always rubbing it in?

253
00:20:06,865 --> 00:20:10,905
Look, wouldn't dialing it back
be better for your relationship?

254
00:20:10,985 --> 00:20:14,425
You know what I've had to go through,
yet you two always side with her.

255
00:20:14,505 --> 00:20:16,785
How many times has her mom insulted me?

256
00:20:16,865 --> 00:20:19,265
She'd even insult
my parents and my brother,

257
00:20:19,345 --> 00:20:21,425
yet Runch never defended me!

258
00:20:21,505 --> 00:20:24,545
Hey. Runch is the mediator.
It must be tough for her.

259
00:20:24,625 --> 00:20:26,265
But is it tough just for her?

260
00:20:26,345 --> 00:20:28,785
Even my family
has never treated me that way.

261
00:20:28,865 --> 00:20:32,185
They raised me so well
just for that old hag to tell me off!

262
00:20:32,265 --> 00:20:33,665
It's tough for me too!

263
00:20:33,745 --> 00:20:37,985
Well, look at her go. She just called
the mother of her dear wife an "old hag."

264
00:20:38,065 --> 00:20:40,425
She's my ex-wife. Please get it right.

265
00:20:41,225 --> 00:20:42,545
You aren't divorced yet.

266
00:20:42,625 --> 00:20:45,505
We will be. Just you wait.

267
00:20:59,185 --> 00:21:01,585
Try this, Runch.

268
00:21:01,665 --> 00:21:03,905
I cooked today, you know!

269
00:21:03,985 --> 00:21:05,665
-Thank you, Mom.
-Of course.

270
00:21:06,985 --> 00:21:09,025
-You too. Dig in.
-Thank you.

271
00:21:09,105 --> 00:21:10,225
Don't be shy.

272
00:21:10,305 --> 00:21:11,945
Help yourself, Runch.

273
00:21:12,025 --> 00:21:15,425
You look like you've lost a lot of weight.
You know that, right?

274
00:21:17,185 --> 00:21:20,305
Yeah. Are you exhausted, honey?

275
00:21:20,385 --> 00:21:22,345
Has work been rough?

276
00:21:22,865 --> 00:21:25,185
Or are you not getting enough rest?

277
00:21:27,185 --> 00:21:30,985
If you're feeling tired or burned out,
and you want to rest, you can tell me.

278
00:21:32,745 --> 00:21:35,665
You know this is like
your second home, right?

279
00:21:38,025 --> 00:21:38,865
Yes, Mom.

280
00:21:43,425 --> 00:21:44,505
Runch,

281
00:21:45,345 --> 00:21:47,385
no matter what happens,

282
00:21:49,225 --> 00:21:51,705
I'll still think of you
as my second daughter.

283
00:21:53,025 --> 00:21:56,625
I really love you
like you're my own daughter.

284
00:22:01,905 --> 00:22:03,465
Thank you.

285
00:22:05,185 --> 00:22:06,065
Come on. Dig in.

286
00:22:06,145 --> 00:22:08,105
-I've got the sour curry too.
-Today's a good day.

287
00:22:08,905 --> 00:22:10,945
I'd like to treat my sister-in-law
to a drink.

288
00:22:14,305 --> 00:22:15,785
Sure.

289
00:22:15,865 --> 00:22:18,345
But just a tiny bit, please.

290
00:22:19,065 --> 00:22:19,985
Nai.

291
00:22:22,305 --> 00:22:25,105
You're a strong woman.
I bet you aren't a lightweight.

292
00:22:25,185 --> 00:22:28,145
Sure. But just a tiny bit, please.

293
00:22:28,225 --> 00:22:30,905
A tiny bit's not enough.
You've got to go all out.

294
00:22:31,985 --> 00:22:33,785
Nai, can you not?

295
00:22:34,505 --> 00:22:35,585
It's okay.

296
00:22:46,025 --> 00:22:47,225
Cheers.

297
00:23:11,225 --> 00:23:12,305
Not too rough.

298
00:23:12,825 --> 00:23:15,065
Two drinks and she's out cold?

299
00:23:17,425 --> 00:23:20,625
You know she's a lightweight,
yet you tried to get her drunk.

300
00:23:21,225 --> 00:23:25,025
Well, it can't be helped.
She asked my sister for a divorce.

301
00:23:26,025 --> 00:23:28,865
She made my sister sad,
so that's what she gets.

302
00:23:29,905 --> 00:23:31,705
You're acting like a child.

303
00:23:34,745 --> 00:23:35,985
She hurt you so bad,

304
00:23:37,665 --> 00:23:38,785
yet you still care about her?

305
00:23:43,465 --> 00:23:44,545
On the day of the divorce,

306
00:23:45,865 --> 00:23:47,385
will you really be able to take it?

307
00:23:48,065 --> 00:23:49,065
That's my question.

308
00:24:08,385 --> 00:24:10,945
You know you're a lightweight.
Why'd you drink so much?

309
00:24:13,985 --> 00:24:17,705
Well, Nai asked me to drink with him.

310
00:24:17,785 --> 00:24:21,305
It would've been rude for me to refuse.

311
00:24:21,385 --> 00:24:23,305
That's what you're worried about?

312
00:24:28,865 --> 00:24:29,825
Why are you smiling?

313
00:24:31,625 --> 00:24:36,425
I'm happy to see that you care about me.

314
00:24:38,505 --> 00:24:40,945
You got me all wrong.
This isn't me caring about you.

315
00:24:41,025 --> 00:24:42,545
I'm scolding you.

316
00:24:46,505 --> 00:24:50,665
If you scold me, I'll be happy too,
because it shows

317
00:24:50,745 --> 00:24:53,145
that you care.

318
00:25:01,665 --> 00:25:04,345
You can go home without me.

319
00:25:04,425 --> 00:25:09,585
I'll call a driver myself.

320
00:25:12,705 --> 00:25:15,625
What are you calling one for?
We're going home together.

321
00:25:16,625 --> 00:25:17,705
Come on.

322
00:25:18,345 --> 00:25:19,625
Just leave your car here.

323
00:25:19,705 --> 00:25:22,785
I'll have my dad's driver
drive it to our house tomorrow, okay?

324
00:25:23,665 --> 00:25:28,105
-Come on.
-You are just the sweetest, Neen.

325
00:25:41,465 --> 00:25:42,945
We're in your room now.

326
00:25:57,865 --> 00:25:59,345
Don't hug me.

327
00:25:59,425 --> 00:26:01,465
We're not the same anymore.

328
00:26:02,345 --> 00:26:06,465
Why not? I remember

329
00:26:07,105 --> 00:26:09,465
you used to like it when I did this.

330
00:26:09,545 --> 00:26:11,265
But right now, we're not…

331
00:26:15,185 --> 00:26:18,185
Right now, we're not the same anymore.

332
00:26:19,225 --> 00:26:20,865
Don't do this again.

333
00:26:59,065 --> 00:27:00,225
Thank you.

334
00:27:26,865 --> 00:27:28,065
What's wrong with it?

335
00:27:32,145 --> 00:27:33,345
What's wrong with the car?

336
00:27:35,305 --> 00:27:38,305
I can't start it. The battery's dead.

337
00:27:38,385 --> 00:27:40,065
I have a meeting today too.

338
00:27:42,265 --> 00:27:44,065
If you can't start it,

339
00:27:44,585 --> 00:27:47,905
why don't you get in my car?
I'll drive you.

340
00:28:02,385 --> 00:28:04,865
Let me go grab a coffee really quick.
Do you need anything?

341
00:28:04,945 --> 00:28:06,065
No.

342
00:28:43,105 --> 00:28:45,705
You're just buying coffee.
What's with all that chit-chat?

343
00:28:48,065 --> 00:28:49,625
Honey!

344
00:28:51,145 --> 00:28:53,225
What's taking you so long?

345
00:28:53,305 --> 00:28:57,145
They had a couple of orders before mine.

346
00:28:57,225 --> 00:28:58,465
What?

347
00:28:58,545 --> 00:29:01,825
Why didn't you tell me?
You took so long I got bored.

348
00:29:01,905 --> 00:29:05,345
This is unacceptable.
You have to make up for it.

349
00:29:07,745 --> 00:29:09,185
Well, what do you want me to do?

350
00:29:10,305 --> 00:29:13,665
Aw, honey. What you used to do, of course.

351
00:29:18,545 --> 00:29:20,345
Come on, honey. Quick.

352
00:29:22,745 --> 00:29:25,025
You are just the sweetest.

353
00:29:25,105 --> 00:29:29,105
-There's my girl! Right?
-Your drink, Ms. Runch.

354
00:29:29,825 --> 00:29:30,865
-Thank you--
-Whoa!

355
00:29:31,665 --> 00:29:32,545
Thank you.

356
00:29:36,025 --> 00:29:37,185
Let's go, honey.

357
00:29:45,625 --> 00:29:47,105
Were you jealous?

358
00:29:47,185 --> 00:29:49,905
I wasn't. I was annoyed, more like.

359
00:29:49,985 --> 00:29:52,985
You seem so close. Do you buy from here
every day or something?

360
00:29:53,065 --> 00:29:55,185
Yes. Every day.

361
00:29:55,265 --> 00:29:58,425
Ugh. Did you want coffee
or did you want something else?

362
00:29:59,345 --> 00:30:01,105
Well, coffee, of course.

363
00:30:01,745 --> 00:30:04,665
There are so many other cafés.
Why'd it have to be this one?

364
00:30:05,505 --> 00:30:06,785
Neen,

365
00:30:07,465 --> 00:30:09,145
don't you remember?

366
00:30:09,225 --> 00:30:11,865
This is our café.

367
00:30:51,265 --> 00:30:52,705
Thanks for the ride.

368
00:31:04,705 --> 00:31:07,865
I'll carry these upstairs for you.
You have a lot to carry.

369
00:31:07,945 --> 00:31:08,985
Don't.

370
00:31:10,465 --> 00:31:13,585
I insist. Don't oppose me.

371
00:31:25,865 --> 00:31:28,585
-Ms. Neen! Hello.
-Hello.

372
00:31:28,665 --> 00:31:30,225
-Hello, Ms. Runch
-Hello.

373
00:31:30,305 --> 00:31:33,345
It's been a while. Where have you been?

374
00:31:34,825 --> 00:31:38,305
I've been busy with work lately,
so I couldn't find the time to come.

375
00:31:39,305 --> 00:31:42,425
That's a relief. And here I thought

376
00:31:42,505 --> 00:31:43,985
you two were fighting.

377
00:31:46,145 --> 00:31:50,025
It's just that you two
are the dream couple for me.

378
00:31:50,105 --> 00:31:54,145
Heck, everyone in our office says
they want a relationship like yours!

379
00:32:14,745 --> 00:32:17,385
I'll take care of your car for you, Neen.

380
00:32:17,465 --> 00:32:19,785
I'll give you a ride home this evening.

381
00:32:20,425 --> 00:32:21,185
Don't.

382
00:32:22,425 --> 00:32:24,145
I can call a ride myself.

383
00:32:25,865 --> 00:32:27,065
No way.

384
00:32:31,625 --> 00:32:35,385
Don't forget, we're the "dream couple."

385
00:32:35,465 --> 00:32:38,225
Don't disappoint everyone now.

386
00:32:38,745 --> 00:32:40,105
See you this evening.

387
00:32:56,585 --> 00:33:00,705
I tell you, if Runch hadn't married
the CEO's granddaughter,

388
00:33:00,785 --> 00:33:04,025
she never would've gotten
to be our boss today.

389
00:33:04,105 --> 00:33:07,345
You're right. Sometimes,
when she makes mistakes,

390
00:33:07,425 --> 00:33:09,105
no one dares to reprimand her.

391
00:33:10,265 --> 00:33:13,705
What kind of boss
has her team do her work for her?

392
00:33:13,785 --> 00:33:17,265
And she's always quiet during meetings.
It's like she's being used as a prop

393
00:33:17,345 --> 00:33:19,505
because it looks good for us
to have a female boss.

394
00:33:19,585 --> 00:33:23,345
I wonder. Is she really that great,
or is it just because

395
00:33:24,025 --> 00:33:25,625
her wife's an heir of Iperis' CEO?

396
00:33:27,185 --> 00:33:31,385
I don't know.
But if I were her, I'd feel so insecure.

397
00:33:31,905 --> 00:33:34,105
She got to marry the CEO's granddaughter,

398
00:33:34,185 --> 00:33:36,905
yet she's still just
an invisible boss to this day.

399
00:33:36,985 --> 00:33:38,505
No one really respects her.

400
00:33:38,585 --> 00:33:41,465
Yeah. Whenever she walks by,
everyone just keeps doing their work.

401
00:33:41,545 --> 00:33:43,225
No one wants to talk to her.

402
00:33:43,305 --> 00:33:45,225
I guess she can't get along with anyone.

403
00:33:46,625 --> 00:33:48,625
She's probably someone

404
00:33:48,705 --> 00:33:52,985
who knows they're incompetent.
That's why she acts calm and quiet

405
00:33:53,065 --> 00:33:54,745
to hide her insecurity.

406
00:34:08,025 --> 00:34:09,145
Hello, Boss.

407
00:34:10,425 --> 00:34:11,905
Would you like a coffee?

408
00:34:45,985 --> 00:34:48,824
Something's wrong
with your car's electrical system.

409
00:34:49,385 --> 00:34:52,105
It'll take days to fix it.

410
00:34:52,185 --> 00:34:54,505
I'll give you a ride until then.

411
00:34:55,185 --> 00:34:56,065
Don't.

412
00:34:57,425 --> 00:35:00,985
I'll ask my dad for a new car
so I don't have to bother you.

413
00:35:01,985 --> 00:35:05,825
For you, it's no bother.

414
00:35:15,705 --> 00:35:17,185
This isn't the way back home!

415
00:35:19,425 --> 00:35:22,345
Let's have dinner first,
then we'll go home.

416
00:35:34,545 --> 00:35:38,985
I ordered your favorite dish. Dig in.

417
00:35:39,545 --> 00:35:40,665
Why are you doing this?

418
00:35:42,265 --> 00:35:43,545
What do you mean?

419
00:35:44,065 --> 00:35:47,225
No one's watching.
Why are you being nice to me?

420
00:35:47,305 --> 00:35:50,025
I just wanted
to do things for you like before.

421
00:35:50,105 --> 00:35:53,425
Like before?
You know nothing's the same as before.

422
00:35:54,505 --> 00:35:56,785
What do you want?
Are you playing mind games with me?

423
00:35:56,865 --> 00:35:58,625
Are you playing with my heart?

424
00:35:58,705 --> 00:36:00,825
That's not what I think.

425
00:36:01,705 --> 00:36:05,385
I just wanted to us to part
with good memories.

426
00:36:05,465 --> 00:36:06,905
There's no need.

427
00:36:06,985 --> 00:36:10,545
All the good memories were gone
when you asked me for a divorce.

428
00:36:11,145 --> 00:36:14,865
So stop being nice
and acting as if you know what I want.

429
00:36:14,945 --> 00:36:18,065
I don't want to be familiar
with having you by my side anymore.

430
00:37:42,345 --> 00:37:44,625
<i>You probably don't want to see my face.</i>

431
00:37:44,705 --> 00:37:46,425
<i>I'm off to work now.</i>

432
00:37:46,505 --> 00:37:49,265
<i>Don't forget to eat all of it. From Runch.</i>

433
00:38:00,065 --> 00:38:02,265
You sure know me well, Runch.

434
00:39:28,065 --> 00:39:29,025
See that dress?

435
00:39:29,105 --> 00:39:31,825
I have one that's blue,
but I don't have a pink one yet.

436
00:39:31,905 --> 00:39:33,545
-You need to get the pink one too.
-Yeah!

437
00:39:33,625 --> 00:39:34,785
-So pretty.
-It's 10% off too.

438
00:39:34,865 --> 00:39:36,545
-See? It's that one right there.
-It's on sale!

439
00:39:36,625 --> 00:39:38,065
-Yeah!
-That's great!

440
00:39:38,145 --> 00:39:39,065
-How great.
-Want to check out that store?

441
00:39:39,145 --> 00:39:40,625
-Yes.
-Isn't that Neen?

442
00:39:41,985 --> 00:39:44,665
It's her! Ging,

443
00:39:44,745 --> 00:39:46,305
isn't that your beautiful daughter-in-law?

444
00:39:46,385 --> 00:39:47,385
I don't think so.

445
00:39:47,465 --> 00:39:49,585
-Hello!
-Neen!

446
00:39:52,025 --> 00:39:54,145
Hello, Mom. Hello, you two.

447
00:39:54,225 --> 00:39:55,465
-Hello.
-Hello.

448
00:39:55,545 --> 00:39:57,465
I'm so glad to meet you, Neen.

449
00:39:57,545 --> 00:39:59,665
Did you get even prettier?

450
00:39:59,745 --> 00:40:01,145
Thank you.

451
00:40:01,225 --> 00:40:04,105
Right, Neen. Ging wants a designer scarf.

452
00:40:04,185 --> 00:40:06,705
She really wants it,
but she said it's too expensive.

453
00:40:06,785 --> 00:40:08,665
It costs 35,000 baht.

454
00:40:08,745 --> 00:40:10,185
Why don't you buy her one?

455
00:40:10,265 --> 00:40:11,705
Of course!

456
00:40:11,785 --> 00:40:12,945
You don't have to.

457
00:40:13,025 --> 00:40:15,345
How can I not?

458
00:40:15,425 --> 00:40:17,625
You're Runch's important person.

459
00:40:17,705 --> 00:40:20,025
Of course I have to take care of you
as best I can.

460
00:40:20,105 --> 00:40:21,625
Please, go for it.

461
00:40:22,225 --> 00:40:24,705
Neen, you're so kind.

462
00:40:24,785 --> 00:40:26,985
She's everyone's dream daughter-in-law.

463
00:40:28,505 --> 00:40:29,945
Why are you quiet?

464
00:40:32,385 --> 00:40:34,065
She's so sweet, isn't she?

465
00:40:34,865 --> 00:40:36,585
Here, Mom.

466
00:40:39,945 --> 00:40:44,185
Don't thank me, Mom.
It was my pleasure to buy it for you.

467
00:40:46,625 --> 00:40:48,905
Oh, and you two.

468
00:40:49,425 --> 00:40:50,945
Today's a good day,

469
00:40:51,025 --> 00:40:53,385
so I bought one for each of you too.

470
00:40:53,465 --> 00:40:55,225
Are you sure, honey?

471
00:40:55,305 --> 00:40:57,265
Of course I am. I'm very sure.

472
00:40:57,345 --> 00:40:59,825
Neen! Thank you so much.

473
00:40:59,905 --> 00:41:01,745
I promise to handle it

474
00:41:01,825 --> 00:41:03,785
-very delicately.
-Yeah.

475
00:41:03,865 --> 00:41:06,105
And are you all going anywhere else?

476
00:41:06,185 --> 00:41:07,505
We're heading to dinner next.

477
00:41:08,025 --> 00:41:09,505
Dinner, you say?

478
00:41:14,025 --> 00:41:16,785
Mom, here's my card.

479
00:41:19,265 --> 00:41:21,585
Please treat your friends to dinner.

480
00:41:22,225 --> 00:41:23,985
Choose whichever restaurant you want.

481
00:41:24,065 --> 00:41:26,665
It's my treat, so please don't hold back.

482
00:41:29,745 --> 00:41:33,025
If you'll excuse me,
I have to go take care of something.

483
00:41:33,105 --> 00:41:33,945
See you later.

484
00:41:34,025 --> 00:41:35,665
-See you later.
-See you later.

485
00:41:35,745 --> 00:41:38,425
Ging, you're so lucky

486
00:41:38,505 --> 00:41:40,145
to have her as your daughter-in-law.

487
00:41:41,785 --> 00:41:43,185
Wow!

488
00:41:43,265 --> 00:41:45,065
I've always wanted it.

489
00:41:45,145 --> 00:41:47,345
It's so pretty.
I'm so happy she bought it for us.

490
00:41:55,025 --> 00:41:56,865
-Why'd you come to see me, Mom?
-Peeracha!

491
00:41:56,945 --> 00:41:59,865
Get out here! Get out here, now!

492
00:42:01,785 --> 00:42:03,545
What's wrong, Mom?

493
00:42:04,105 --> 00:42:07,505
Why don't you ask your cheeky wife
what she did to me?

494
00:42:09,985 --> 00:42:12,065
You did that in front of my friends.

495
00:42:12,145 --> 00:42:15,225
That was so demeaning.
You acted as if I'm living off of you.

496
00:42:17,865 --> 00:42:19,305
How was that my fault?

497
00:42:19,385 --> 00:42:21,065
I just wanted to treat
an old lady to dinner

498
00:42:21,145 --> 00:42:22,905
so she wouldn't starve to death.

499
00:42:22,985 --> 00:42:24,065
You!

500
00:42:24,145 --> 00:42:26,345
Mom, that's enough. Let's get outside.

501
00:42:26,425 --> 00:42:27,425
Stay out of this!

502
00:42:27,505 --> 00:42:29,265
-Mom, please get outside!
-Runch!

503
00:42:29,345 --> 00:42:31,065
Did you just yell at me?

504
00:42:31,145 --> 00:42:32,785
You yelled at me because of her?!

505
00:42:33,905 --> 00:42:35,345
How annoying!

506
00:42:36,505 --> 00:42:37,625
Mom!

507
00:42:55,945 --> 00:42:56,905
Neen…

508
00:43:11,785 --> 00:43:12,625
Mom.

509
00:43:15,065 --> 00:43:16,505
Get out.

510
00:43:19,785 --> 00:43:21,025
Go.

511
00:43:25,225 --> 00:43:26,225
Runch.

512
00:43:26,745 --> 00:43:27,665
Runch.

513
00:43:29,785 --> 00:43:31,585
Runch, I didn't mean it!

514
00:43:57,505 --> 00:44:00,105
3 YEARS AGO

515
00:44:09,145 --> 00:44:11,945
Your shirt's all dirty.
Do you want to get changed?

516
00:44:12,545 --> 00:44:13,585
It's okay.

517
00:44:14,185 --> 00:44:17,745
It's almost time to clock out,
and I don't have a spare shirt.

518
00:44:19,185 --> 00:44:22,585
But if your white shirt gets wet,
it'll be too revealing.

519
00:44:23,185 --> 00:44:26,865
If you don't mind, you can borrow mine.
I've never worn it before.

520
00:44:36,265 --> 00:44:37,785
I don't want to bother you.

521
00:44:43,105 --> 00:44:45,025
Please take my blouse.

522
00:44:45,985 --> 00:44:48,305
You'll get sick in that wet shirt.

523
00:44:49,865 --> 00:44:51,745
Let me go get it from my car.

524
00:45:06,105 --> 00:45:07,625
Thank you.

525
00:45:07,705 --> 00:45:09,345
I'll give it back as soon as I can.

526
00:45:10,385 --> 00:45:11,585
Can I…

527
00:45:12,945 --> 00:45:14,625
have your email address?

528
00:45:14,705 --> 00:45:16,065
Email?

529
00:45:17,625 --> 00:45:19,465
It's easier to call me on my number.

530
00:45:20,585 --> 00:45:21,785
Can I have your phone?

531
00:45:26,705 --> 00:45:28,025
Done.

532
00:45:28,105 --> 00:45:30,465
My name is Neen. What's your name?

533
00:45:30,545 --> 00:45:31,985
My name is Runch.

534
00:45:32,065 --> 00:45:33,945
Do you work around here?

535
00:45:34,025 --> 00:45:35,705
Yes. Pretty close.

536
00:45:36,545 --> 00:45:38,145
Nice to meet you, Ms. Runch.

537
00:46:31,425 --> 00:46:33,985
Does she think having connections
and a rich wife means

538
00:46:34,065 --> 00:46:35,825
she can act all high-and-mighty here?

539
00:46:35,905 --> 00:46:37,465
Be a man.

540
00:46:37,545 --> 00:46:40,145
There are many more things we can do

541
00:46:40,225 --> 00:46:42,385
to make it look like
we really love each other.

542
00:46:42,465 --> 00:46:43,905
Then do it all.

543
00:46:45,465 --> 00:46:47,145
You know Neen hates my guts.

544
00:46:47,225 --> 00:46:49,225
But you hate her too, don't you?

545
00:46:52,705 --> 00:46:53,625
Cut it out!

546
00:47:39,585 --> 00:47:41,585
Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

